Author: Sibin
Last Update: Dec-24-2016
Test Enviorment: Mac 10.12.2

################################
This Project can help you customize your word-of-the-day screen saver on your Mac. 

################################
!!Before You Use
The Origin "NOAD_wotd_list.txt" and "New Oxford American Dictionary.dictionary" might be discarded. Please back up before your use.

################################
About SIC : System Integrity Protection"

You may face the SIC issue for Mac OS after 10.11
To disable it temporarily:
1. boot into recovery mode: restart your Mac and hold Command+R as it boots.
2. Utility -> Terminal"
3. csrutil status"
4. Now Make it :  csrutil disable"
5. after you finished your task : csrutil enable"



################################

-----------Step 1---------------
Disable SIC

-----------Step 2---------------
Edit your own data.txt in the form below:

index \t Word \t Define of the Word

-----------Step 3---------------
make all

-----------Step 4---------------
make install

-----------Step 5---------------
Swith your system screen saver to "Word of The Day"

-----------Step 6---------------
Enjoy it!

